        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I have used Infusion a few times during really close fights where the mana is super tight.  For example:</P><P>Guild is fighting Emperor Ssra.  This is a VERY long fight, VERY mana intensive.  If a cleric or chanter goes down, they have to be back in action RIGHT NOW! They cannot wait for you to regen mana ( even with Arch Lich, bard song ) if you are low at that particular moment. Burn an EE and get 1k mana that you can immediately begin dumping to get a critical member back in action FAST.</P><P>Back before SoL and all the fancy mana regen that came with it, Infusion got used alot to fill up a wizzy's mana pool to help finish mobs fast.  This was about one of the only real options for stretching mana in really close fights before SoL.  Old mod rods just didn't cut it.  Velketor wiped you at 2% heath?.. damn should have asked the necros to burn a few EE's for the wizzys ( or clerics, wherever the weak link may be ).</P><P>Vtyn<BR>Warlock<BR>Heaven and Earth</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
